<TITLE> Mahasweta Devi meets PM </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jan 30 (bdnews24.com)  Mahasweta Devi, one of India's leading writers and social activists, met prime minister Sheikh Hasina at her Sudha Sadan home Friday. Devi, visiting Dhaka in connection with Chobi Mela-V, "Asia's largest photography festival", formally opened the show featuring works of artists from 33 countries at the National Museum Friday. The festival also features a video conference between Devi and two other outstanding individuals, Noam Chomsky and Stuart Hall, who will provide their take on 'Freedom' the theme of this year's Mela. bdnews
